# Commit Style

When creating a git commit, follow
[`docs/standards/conventional-commits.md`](../../docs/standards/conventional-commits.md):
use the `<type>[scope][!]: <description>` format, with type being feat/fix/docs/refactor/test/...,
scope being a module, package, or core subsystem, and breaking changes marked with `!` or a `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer.

Commit messages MUST be written in English, regardless of the chat language.
